In Need for Speed: The Run, you compete across America.
Reviewing
A trip, in principle carefree, is complicated by a series of improper oversights of a routine trip during the morning shift.
To a certain extent, the expectations were met, but this is of no use if, in reality, nothing extraordinary was intended to be done.
The new installment, to which the title is added The Run, aroused great expectations even before its premiere.
It promised to give new airs to the old Need for Speed racing saga and, as shown, it appears as a game that should not end up again being a genre of action without more.
We also felt curious to know how the scenes would be inserted, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As usually happens in NFS series, the results do not vary much from what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in the total count points are lost due to absurd failures, which have already been appearing in the series for years.
In reality they cannot even be called mistakes, but rather it is the incomprehensible disdain of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, you are offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco, and your mission is to get to New York first.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than fifty races.
From this it follows that each race takes place by a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite diverse and interesting.
Thus, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the graphic is equivalent to that of previous installments of the series.
Therefore, it is nothing of the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are occasionally diversified by an atypical element.
Thus, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you must be careful not to be buried by an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that’s enough.
For a moment, you try to overtake a required number of rivals (normally in a classic race), then you try to save time (timed classic duel) and then a duel awaits you against a single opponent.
In the middle of all this sometimes appears the police, who does nothing but make things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than you might expect (in particular there are only three).
But the end result is positive, because this element does not get annoying and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of previous episodes.
That means that today it is no longer a big thing, but you can not claim that it is bad.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you can already look elsewhere.
But a race designed with enough action is quite suitable for this style of driving, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, everything is in order.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, the same is no longer the case with collisions.
From games of this type can not be expected to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a hit against any object, you can not predict how your car will react, with which everything is not in order.
It is typical that, when making a very tight overtaking or circulating the car with normal traffic, there are only slight frictions, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or even completely destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no big problems arise, but it can put you in a bad mood.
Resets are scheduled in such a way that, when you suffer an accident or get off the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, in each race only five resets are available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's just a help in case something goes wrong, but it's not very reliable.
Sometimes, reset doesn’t help, it only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A big disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you will find yourself somewhere "civil" vehicles always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes you rage especially in situations, when you see that two cars going to meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or brake.
It doesn’t matter when you arrive, because it’s programmed because the “surprise” will always happen in front of your noses.
Opponents also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will reach places where, regardless of the time, you will always be advanced by the same opponent in the same place.
In addition, this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at whatever price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming from the front, so at first you can spoil the car.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it will surely disappoint you right away.
And it’s a shame, because even though the travel model is simple, the game is fun and action-packed, so it’s often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn’t matter, whether the merit is taken the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or qualifying in the race so that it doesn’t fit the boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is to change cars during races.
You have to pay attention to the gas supplies next to the road, because right there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases what you have will be enough.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and exotic super sports cars for technical driving, for example, on mountain roads with curves.
In addition, the main narrative thread also appears a parallel thread of challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know by the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which is useful for both challenges and stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog function is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community functions.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
By car you reach the tunnel of the metro (pass), where you can run in the dark on the roads (pass).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, behind you comes the subway convoy and is taken in front of you without more.
In the newsroom we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game no one thought even a little or if the authors really take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even superb.
Well, what a pity that, in the most tense moments, the image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when the continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "Each of his father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for their music.
The final feel of Need for Speed: The Run is quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble asserting that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not finished.
The fun is assured, but get ready because the mistakes will hit you in the eye with the strength of some airport reflectors.
