On the other hand, conservatives argue that it is Magistrate Elena Kagan, who has an ethical problem, not Scalia and Thomas.
Kagan served as Attorney General of the Obama administration when the first legal challenges to the law were presented in the first instance court.
Her critics have pressed Kagan to refrain from seeing the case, saying she was too involved in defending the law to now be impartial.
Kagan has given no indication that he will.
