In an appendix to her letters to McCain and Graham, Panetta enunciates new details of how the reductions “generate significant operational risks: delays in response time to crises, conflicts and disasters; severely limits our ability to be previously deployed and compromised around the world; and poses an unacceptable risk in future combat operations.”
And Panetta said some of the biggest defense projects could face the axe, including those that are already being tested and some just in the early stages of planning.
