The Secretariat of Communications and Transport (SCT) reported that the results cast on the accident where the Secretary of Government, Francisco Blake Mora, and seven other people lost their lives, indicate that the helicopter impacted directly on the ground in complete structural integrity, without the pilot being able to attempt a forced landing.
During a press conference, Dionisio Pérez J<0xC3><0xA1>come, Secretary of Communications and Transport, mentioned that before taking off the aircraft, the pilot found that the weather conditions were suitable for flying.
"The elements that seem to indicate that the unit had several contacts with the ground, the blades had contact with trees at 25 meters where the unit lost the fuselage."
It also reported that the unit was designed for 19 people, so it had the necessary requirements to transport personnel.
In addition, he said that the research done in the impact area does not report the appearance of parts on the ground.
“In a search it is reported that there are no parts or components of the ship elsewhere, the impact was presented structurally.
"The design of the helicopter was for 19 passengers, it had adequate requirements to carry passengers.
The terrain has a seven-degree slope at 30 degrees of inclination.
