This was the work of the cale<0xC3><0xB1>o that identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A Lofoscopist from Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the death of Alfonso Cano.
The work of these officials is key.
On November 4th, a Lofoscopist from the CTI of Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the identity of the top FARC chief: "Alfonso Cano", through the collation of his fingerprints.
Of the seven lofoscopists working in the CTI sectional, that week Eliazar Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the area of judicial research for 21 years, was on the “availability” shift.
At the beginning of his career, Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez worked in Choc<0xC3><0xB3> municipalities, where he often had to spend more than five days in the jungle to get to the site where the bodies were to be identified.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after completing the corresponding courses, he specialized in lofoscopy, which is the study of the skin of friction, that is, of the palms of the hands and feet.
The week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano to Eliazar warned him to wear minimum clothing for three days.
Something big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he went out for the Cauca in a helicopter from Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected of being the man who led the oldest guerrilla in the world, so they asked him to carry the decadactylary card of Guillermo Leon Saenz (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the research team at the site where the body was located, he did not recognize it for its physical appearance, as it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He was beardless, dressed like a peasant in the area, without glasses and much thinner.
But the fingerprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a transplanter and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse to those of the card.
His eye did not fail him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was in charge of confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinz<0xC3><0xB3>n, that he was the head of the FARC.
In Search of the Footprint
For a typewriter of the Sij<0xC3><0xAD>n de Cali, the recognition made by President Juan Manuel Santos to Eliazar Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez, in the press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
Many people do not know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science, with no margin for error, that can become key in solving crimes.
Apart from the identification of corpses, the Lofoscopists support investigations for crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identity of the people captured.
When caught, many criminals present false ballots or have no papers.
We take their fingerprints and look for them in the database.
The investigator said that in a case of theft, he had to remove a piece of wall from a house, because in that place the thief had supported his hand to get out a safe full of jewelry and money.
“The walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces to make a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to get the fingerprint of the whole hand and identify the criminal, who had participated in different thefts,” he said.
Traces can also rule out or reassert suspects in murder cases.
They recently found a dead man, with bottles of liquor around him.
The investigation determined that a relative could be a suspect in the crime, and indeed a print on the bottle coincided.
Although this does not guarantee that he was the killer, it does place him at the scene of the crime.
A CTI fingerprinter explained that in the objects "the fingerprints are taken with chemical or physical reagents."
When they appear, a transplanter or tape is used to lift them.
After this, the prints are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registry.
"The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians," the ITC expert said.
He clarified that not everything is as shown on the CSI television program.
Just as not everything that shines is gold, not everything that is touched becomes a footprint.
However, if it can be used, if the respective collation is performed.
