The court order prohibits authorities from evicting Occupy Wall Street members or enforcing “laws that were issued after the occupation began or prohibiting protesters from re-accessing the park with shops or other properties they used previously.”
Mayor Bloomberg told the press that, because of that court order, the city had suspended the reopening of the space to the public and the protesters, who he warned, however, that local laws do not allow them to re-install themselves with tents and sleeping bags.
